msgstr ""

#: ../../api/generated/chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.rst:11:<autosummary>:1
#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:1 of
msgid "Estimate the normalised power-spectral density of ``x`` via Welch."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:3 of
msgid ""
"The PSD is one-sided, peak-normalised to ``1.0``, and the frequency axis "
"is returned as ``ω/π`` for consistency with the notation used in the "
"project figures (x-axis of every PSD panel)."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised of
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:7 of
msgid "Input signal, shape ``(N,)``. Can be any dtype coercible to ``float``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:9 of
msgid ""
"Length of the FFT. Larger values give smoother spectra at the cost of "
"more computation. Must be ``>= window_length``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:11 of
msgid ""
"Length of the Welch segment (aka ``nperseg``). Controls the frequency "
"resolution."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:13 of
msgid ""
"Sampling frequency. Leave at the default ``1.0`` to work in normalised "
"units — the output axis becomes ``ω/π`` directly."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:15 of
msgid ""
"If ``True`` (default), the DC component of ``x`` is subtracted before the"
" FFT to avoid a spurious spike at ``ω = 0``. Set to ``False`` only if you"
" explicitly want to see the DC bin."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:18 of
msgid ""
"Welch window. Supported values: ``\"hamming\"`` (default), ``\"hann\"``, "
"``\"blackman\"``, ``\"kaiser\"``, ``\"blackmanharris\"``, ``\"boxcar\"``,"
" ``\"bartlett\"``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:21 of
msgid ""
"Shape parameter of the Kaiser window. Must be ``>= 0``; ignored when "
"``window != \"kaiser\"``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised of
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:24 of
msgid ""
"* **omega_norm** (*ndarray, shape (nfft // 2 + 1,)*) -- Normalised "
"frequency axis, ``ω/π ∈ [0, 1]``. * **psd** (*ndarray, shape (nfft // 2 +"
" 1,)*) -- Peak-normalised PSD. ``psd.max() == 1.0`` unless the input is"
"   identically zero."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:24 of
msgid ""
"**omega_norm** (*ndarray, shape (nfft // 2 + 1,)*) -- Normalised "
"frequency axis, ``ω/π ∈ [0, 1]``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:25 of
msgid ""
"**psd** (*ndarray, shape (nfft // 2 + 1,)*) -- Peak-normalised PSD. "
"``psd.max() == 1.0`` unless the input is identically zero."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised of
msgid "Return type"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:29 of
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.spectral.psd_normalised:30 of
msgid ""
"Welch's method divides ``x`` into overlapping segments, applies the "
"window, takes the periodogram of each, and averages the result. This "
"trades frequency resolution (controlled by ``window_length``) for "
"variance reduction, which is the right trade-off for visualising the "
"smooth broadband spectrum of a chaotic carrier."
msgstr ""

